-- Samsung to Build Water Treatment Plant for Membranes, NHK Says
-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 2012-09-13T15:34:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-13/samsung-to-build-water-treatment-plant-for-membranes-nhk-says.html
A Samsung Group unit plans to build
a plant in the southern coastal Korean city of Yeosu to make
membranes for water treatment, NHK reported, without citing
anyone.  The company, which will begin supplying the membrane
filtering system as early as next April, is expected to formally
announce the plan to enter the water recycling business next
week at an exhibit in Busan, the  news agency  said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
